Another, more common definition of Deism is contrary to being equated with Christianity, as a belief that the Creator then set things in motion to allow the universe and life, but then left things to their own accord; he/she/it doesn't step in and do miracles or judge individuals on belief or merits, etc. This is closer to pantheism, in that the will or mind of the creator is best known by examination and interrogation of the universe as it is. Revelation and prayer and salvation have nothing to do with any of it.<br>
