I know religion has been the excuse for a lot of nastiness (I am no fan of religion, and this includes rabid atheists), but it is not the reason. Call me an old softie, but economics is at the root of almost all-human conflict. Case’s in point:<br>
<br>
Church feared loss of finances and influence due to rise of Protestantism, so they instituted the Inquisition.<br>
<br>
To keep Europeans from killing each other, the Church pointed them to Jerusalem and kept them busy with the Crusades – ensuring economic gains and solidifying political power.<br>
<br>
Of course, I must admit the atheists’ nations of the world have been such models of morality. One has but to look at the USSR and its wonderful human rights record.<br>
<br>
Okay, rant over. As for the pledge, it needs to go. Not because of the god part, but we shouldn’t pledge ourselves to a nation without caveat, and our children should not be forced to do so just because they are in a government school. Patriotism is fine, but it shouldn’t be coerced. Now if someone wants to have a Flag club that says the pledge, more power to them.  <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/alien.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
